AUDIENCE: There are so many
different kinds of donuts.

00:09:47.560 --> 00:09:48.220
KENNY NGUYEN:
Exactly, there's so

00:09:48.220 --> 00:09:50.010
many different kinds of donuts.

00:09:50.010 --> 00:09:50.609
What else?

00:09:50.609 --> 00:09:51.900
AUDIENCE: They taste delicious.

00:09:51.900 --> 00:09:54.910
KENNY NGUYEN: They
taste delicious.

00:09:54.910 --> 00:09:57.330
Come on guys, this is the
time to rise up and talk

00:09:57.330 --> 00:09:57.873
about donuts.

00:09:57.873 --> 00:09:58.580
AUDIENCE: They're flling.

00:09:58.580 --> 00:09:59.102
KENNY NGUYEN: They're filling.

00:09:59.102 --> 00:10:00.280
AUDIENCE: They make you happy.

00:10:00.280 --> 00:10:01.714
KENNY NGUYEN: They
make you happy.

00:10:01.714 --> 00:10:02.900
AUDIENCE: Sugar rush.

00:10:02.900 --> 00:10:04.057
KENNY NGUYEN: Sugar rush.

00:10:04.057 --> 00:10:05.140
AUDIENCE: They're America.

00:10:05.140 --> 00:10:08.450
KENNY NGUYEN: They're
America, there you go.

00:10:08.450 --> 00:10:10.420
So let's create this
central argument.

00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:12.450
For the donut lovers
in here, what if we can

00:10:12.450 --> 00:10:15.890
say that donuts make you happy?

00:10:15.890 --> 00:10:18.140
That's a good enough reason
why people should believe,

00:10:18.140 --> 00:10:21.320
because I don't think anyone in
this room wants to be unhappy.

00:10:21.320 --> 00:10:24.020
Now let's think of
a call to action.

00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:26.550
And I always say when you create
a presentation-- no matter

00:10:26.550 --> 00:10:29.020
what it is-- think about the
call to action at the end.

00:10:29.020 --> 00:10:30.490
Where do we want to lead people?

00:10:30.490 --> 00:10:32.630
Where do we want to take
them on this journey?

00:10:32.630 --> 00:10:35.610
Because if you have a big
idea and you have an argument,

00:10:35.610 --> 00:10:38.240
there's always a chance
