00:41:53.330 --> 00:41:57.460
room in front of people, you
make that deck completely

00:41:57.460 --> 00:42:00.556
separate from what your
actual information is.

00:42:00.556 --> 00:42:03.180
So you can work on your deck, if
you like to display everything

00:42:03.180 --> 00:42:05.730
in PowerPoint or
Keynote or whatever,

00:42:05.730 --> 00:42:08.820
you like to put all
your bullet points in

00:42:08.820 --> 00:42:11.010
and what you want them to
remember and take away,

00:42:11.010 --> 00:42:12.710
make all of that first.

00:42:12.710 --> 00:42:14.840
And then make what you're
gonna present after that.

00:42:14.840 --> 00:42:16.420
Make what you're gonna
present as a completely

00:42:16.420 --> 00:42:18.380
different document
that doesn't live on,

00:42:18.380 --> 00:42:20.380
because that needs you.

00:42:20.380 --> 00:42:21.757
So that's the way
we-- and that's

00:42:21.757 --> 00:42:23.590
a hard thing to remember,
because it's not--

00:42:23.590 --> 00:42:25.184
you're not doubling your work.

00:42:25.184 --> 00:42:27.100
Because in the end, you
just put all your work

00:42:27.100 --> 00:42:28.844
into your structure
and your content,

00:42:28.844 --> 00:42:30.510
and then just spend
the last bit of time

00:42:30.510 --> 00:42:33.290
making a really simplistic deck
so people aren't overloaded

00:42:33.290 --> 00:42:34.370
in trying to read that.

